                <h1>State Agriculture Mechanization Scheme</h1>
                <h3>Description:</h3>
                <p>This scheme is to promote agricultural mechanization and increase the use of energy in agriculture up to 2 kW / ha.
                </p>
                <h3>Objective:</h3>
                <p>To extend the benefits of agricultural mechanization to areas where energy use in agriculture is low and to small and
                marginal farmers.
                Creating awareness among the participants through demonstrations and manpower development.

                </p>
        
                <h3>Eligibility criteria:</h3>
                <p>• It is mandatory for the farmer to have Aadhar card<br>
                • The farmer should have 7/12 transcript and 8A<br>
                • Farmers App. Caste certificate is required if the caste is in Scheduled Tribes<br>
                • Grant will be payable for only one tool i.e. tractor or machine / tool<br>
                • If the tractor is in the name of the person in the family, he will be eligible for the benefit of tractor driven
                implements but proof of being a tractor must be attached.<br>
                • If you have availed benefits for one component / tool, you cannot apply for the same component / tool for next 10
                years but you can apply for other tools<br>

                </p>
          
                <h3>Documents require to get benefit of the scheme:</h3>
                <p> • Aadhaar card<br>
                • Excerpt 7/12<br>
                • 8A certificate<br>
                • Quotation of equipment to be procured and inspection report given by the Central Government accredited inspection body<br>
                • Caste Certificate (for Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes)<br>
                • Self declaration<br>
                • Pre-consent letter<br>

        
                </p>
            </div>
